### Plotting an Orbit Over Time

Let's make a time-series plot: iteration number on the x-axis, value on the y-axis.

```scheme
(define (iterate f x0 n)
  (if (<= n 0)
      '()
      (let ((next (f x0)))
        (cons x0 (iterate f next (- n 1))))))

(define (index-list lst)
  (let loop ((i 0) (remaining lst))
    (if (null? remaining)
        '()
        (cons (list i (car remaining))
              (loop (+ i 1) (cdr remaining))))))

(define f-half-plus-1 (lambda (x) (+ (/ x 2) 1)))
(define orbit (iterate f-half-plus-1 10 30))
(define points (index-list orbit))

(plot/render-svg
  (plot/scatter points))
```

[VISUAL: Graphing calculator, Cartesian grid. Points descending smoothly from 10 toward 2 as iteration increases.]

<!-- BUILD: run as standalone; render scatter plot -->

The orbit's convergence is now a visual descent.

