## §6. Recurrence Relations and Fixed Points Revisited

A **recurrence relation** defines a sequence by a formula involving previous terms. We've been iterating them all along.

Example: `a(n+1) = (a(n) + 2/a(n)) / 2` (the Babylonian method for `√2`).

```scheme
(define (iterate f x0 n)
  
")
